trans-unit.source: Log into the [Azure Management Portal], click **Mobile Services**, and then click your app.
trans-unit.target: Log into the [Azure Management Portal], click **Mobile Services**, and then click your app.

trans-unit.source: Click the **Data** tab, and then click **Create**.
trans-unit.target: Click the **Data** tab, and then click **Create**.

trans-unit.source: This displays the **Create new table** dialog.
trans-unit.target: This displays the **Create new table** dialog.

trans-unit.source: Keeping the default **Anybody with the application key** setting for all permissions, type _Registrations_ in **Table name**, and then click the check button.
trans-unit.target: Keeping the default **Anybody with the application key** setting for all permissions, type _Registrations_ in **Table name**, and then click the check button.

trans-unit.source: This creates the **Registrations** table, which stores the channel URIs used to send push notifications.
trans-unit.target: This creates the **Registrations** table, which stores the channel URIs used to send push notifications.

trans-unit.source: Next, you will modify the your app to enable push notifications.
trans-unit.target: Next, you will modify the your app to enable push notifications.
